I came here looking for a quick salad to go as I am a GSU student who is often in a rush and this spot was close to my next class. The reviews seemed promising so I stopped in. The student discount was a great incentive as well. As soon as I walked in the place was empty but I was not greeted at all and the cashier seemed uninterested in helping me.  The chicken salad platter I got was bland at best with not enough trimmings for the price of $8 for the salad alone. And that's with the discount. There are plenty of better options in the area. Save your money for elsewhere.
